sentences: Anna Murashige (村重 杏奈, Murashige An'na, born July 29, 1998) is a Russo-Japanese tarento and a former member of the idol groups HKT48 and NMB48 represented by Twin Planet.
On July 10, 2011, Murashige passed the first generation audition for HKT48.
")On March 4, 2012, when HKT48's Team H was formed, she was selected as one of its 16 members.
On August 17, 2012, she appeared in the TV drama Majisuka Gakuen 3.
In June 2014 she placed 67th in the AKB48 general elections.
On September 22, 2020, she was tested positive for COVID-19.
On September 19, 2021, Murashige announced her graduation from HKT48.
HKT48 official profile at the Wayback Machine (archived March 16, 2021)
On November 26, she debuted at the HKT48 Theater.
She was unveiled along with other HKT48 members on October 23.
She recovered from the disease on October 16.
Her graduation performance was on December 27.
